From: ArcBoost Builder <build@arcboost.local>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 22:13:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 08/13] ArcBoost: rename python-package/lightgbm/ to
 python-package/arcboost/
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Critical patch for the user-facing import path. After this lands:

    import arcboost
    from arcboost import LGBMRegressor, Dataset, train

are the canonical entry points. All 19 internal cross-module imports inside
the package are relative ('from .basic import ...'), so the rename is purely
mechanical: rename the directory, update python-package/pyproject.toml's
[project].name from 'lightgbm' to 'arcboost', and bump the version to
0.1.0.dev0.

Internal class names (LGBMRegressor, LGBMClassifier, Booster, Dataset,
etc.) are preserved on purpose — they're widely-known and documented under
those names; renaming them to ArcBoostRegressor would break drop-in
substitution for users migrating from a vanilla LightGBM workflow.

Note: the compiled C library is still produced as lib_lightgbm.{so,dylib,dll}
and discovered by libpath.py via parents[1]/parents[0] traversal — the
filename stays unchanged because (a) renaming it costs ABI bookkeeping for
zero user benefit and (b) keeping the upstream CMake target name minimizes
patch-rebase friction during future LightGBM bumps.
